text: Navaratnas is a group of nine extraordinary people in an emperor's court in India. Some people to have Navaratnas in their course are Hindu emperor Vikramaditya, the Mughal emperor Akbar, and the feudal lord Raja Krishnachandra. == Vikramaditya's Navaratnas == Vikramaditya's Navaratnas include: == Akbar's Navaratnas == Category:History of India
